```
                    REGULATORY GAP IN ACCOUNT FREEZING
                              
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                      NORMATIVE LAYER                        │
│  (What should exist based on best practices & principles)  │
│                                                             │
│  ▸ Clear Authority  ▸ Due Process  ▸ Time Limits          │
│  ▸ Accountability   ▸ Coordination                         │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                            ▼
                       ╔═══════╗
                       ║  GAP  ║ ← [Evidence from 50 cases]
                       ╚═══════╝
                            ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                       ACTUAL LAYER                          │
│        (What exists in RBI circulars & practice)           │
│                                                             │
│  ▸ Vague "appropriate action"   ▸ No procedures            │
│  ▸ No time limits  ▸ No accountability  ▸ Ad-hoc reporting │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                            ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                         IMPACTS                             │
│                                                             │
│  Account Holders: Arbitrary freezes, indefinite duration   │
│  Banks: Legal uncertainty, excessive litigation            │
│  Courts: 200 cases/day in Kerala HC alone                 │
│  Law Enforcement: Delayed info, missed opportunities       │
│  Economy: Trust erosion, crime facilitation                │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Save this as:** `analysis/gap_map_visual.png` (create in PowerPoint/draw.io and export)

